The paper deals with the problem of 3D face reconstruction and dense face alignment from a single 2D image, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The proposed method uses self-supervised learning and deep neural networks, which are typical techniques in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning from limited data, which is a common challenge in machine learning, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also involves modeling and optimization, which are common topics in artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves geometric modeling and rendering, which are common topics in computer graphics, suggesting cs.GR (Computer Graphics) as the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image and video processing, which are common topics in multimedia, suggesting cs.MM (Multimedia) as the fifth likely sub-category.
